{
  "name": "RPlog_An_Offer_She_Can_t_Refuse",
  "title": "An Offer She Can't Refuse",
  "summary": "In the morning bustle of the Via Ble'Sha market on O'Paal Major, the scarred drifter Morganna Tazecks is approached by the hooded Atrox, now revealed as Lord Director of the Imperial Ubiqtorate. Over coffee, Atrox probes Morganna's rootless life and unfulfilled longing for a home on Caspar before making his pitch: an appointment as Imperial Ambassador to Caspar, complete with staff, autonomy, and the backing of Imperial High Command. He frames the post as a cause for a rebel without one, promising power, fame, and protection from her old enemies. Wrestling with self-doubt and her reluctance to sign her life to the Empire, Morganna ultimately accepts, shaking Atrox's hand and taking the sealed appointment datapad. Atrox instructs her to present it to a man in a red coat in three days to begin her training, then slips away into the shadows.",
